@5210 = ~Eh? What’s this, then? Hah! Now there’s a sight I never thought I’d see. These pieces—aye, I’d wager they’re fragments of the old elven sword they called "The Blade of Day and Night". Haven’t seen craft like this since the Time o’ Songs.~
@5211 = ~Hand me both parts, together with a Sunstone gem and a Moonstone gem, and I’ll see if I can set 'em right again. Won’t come cheap, mind ye: 10000 gold for the forge, the tempering oils, and a fair bit o’ dwarven sweat. But ye’ll be gettin’ a blade worthy o’ the old days, sure enough.~
@5212 = ~Here. Take the fragments — and the gold.~
@5213 = ~Not this time. Do I have something else you could work on?~
@5214 = ~Aye, then. I’ll be here, same as always, if ye change yer mind.~
